</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B575183585F185F9217120074823F337" pageId="19" pageNumber="23" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="88FE51465C76398FEDC8C427FA0B4AC5" pageId="19" pageNumber="23" type="mainText">Habitat. Seashores, fields and railway areas on sandy soil; tips, ports, mills and factories.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CFAB06C99137D6C2616504FF43B821E0" pageId="19" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="84477EA9038FFDE9E095FC88543427AC" pageId="19" pageNumber="23" type="mainText">
Taxonomy. 
<taxonomicName id="B0DC4D76FE412FA252D3C53624AF6A8C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="striatiforme">C. striatiforme</taxonomicName>
was earlier regarded as an infraspecific taxon, first under 
<taxonomicName id="F7C2A0E8F0C5AA5EC57066E8D0AF0384" authority="NaN" authorityName="(e.g. Aellen" authorityYear="1960" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" genus.bestMatchDistance="1944" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="album">
C. album 
<authority id="2385C8D7FF9D7F60726DADDE0436F9FF" pageId="19" pageNumber="23">(e.g. Aellen 1960-61)</authority>
</taxonomicName>
and later under 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B2A8680ABBE2D8FEFD03B74AD0FD1" authority="" authorityName="(Jorgensen" authorityYear="1973" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" genus.bestMatchDistance="267" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="strictum">
C. strictum 
<authority id="36859D4AE77F9210D20A373E2A174E85" pageId="19" pageNumber="23">
(
<normalizedToken id="2E07E775C65F3625C5D9082AE6D7F9B8" originalValue="Jørgensen" pageId="19" pageNumber="23">Jorgensen</normalizedToken>
1973, Uotila 1977a)
</authority>
</taxonomicName>
. It is closer to 
<taxonomicName id="C90365660BA2A7FD601F01C307D70D6F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" genus.bestMatchDistance="219" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="strictum">C. strictum</taxonomicName>
, but in some respects it is intermediate between 
<taxonomicName id="ADE63F37FF6D64DFBB1851812AB179FB" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" genus.bestMatchDistance="2076" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="album">C. album</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F24A4D4D71E890892499B6C6FB0E7504" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" genus.bestMatchDistance="171" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="strictum">C. strictum</taxonomicName>
. In cultivation experiments it proved very uniform and clearly different from 
<taxonomicName id="741FF63C7B807F53F29ED38D5133B28B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" genus.bestMatchDistance="126" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="strictum">C. strictum</taxonomicName>
, and species rank seems more suitable.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
